        </item>
        <item>
            <title>【專訪】香港最後一本 Game 書《GAME WEEKLY》停刊，主編電玩太郎分享 27 年對香港 Game 迷情懷</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2024/12/19/gw/people-interview/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=gw</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2024/12/19/gw/people-interview/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[天恩]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2024 13:15:11 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[人物專訪]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[業界專訪]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[遊戲情報]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[GAME WEEKLY]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1282542</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>1997 年創刊的《GAME WEEKLY》伴隨香港遊戲玩家走過了 27 年的光陰，從紅白機到 PS5，見證了遊戲界的變遷。這本紙媒遊戲雜誌最近宣佈停刊，引發本地玩家對過去那段「等書出攻略」的懷舊歲月無限追憶。靈魂人物電玩太郎最近就接受我們 unwire 訪問，一起回顧這段歷史，並分享他對本地遊戲文化的熱情與展望。</p><h2>全訪問影片 :</h2><div class="epyt-video-wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy"  style="display: block; margin: 0px auto;"  id="_ytid_62045"  width="590" height="332"  data-origwidth="590" data-origheight="332" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ns0CSBmPJcc?enablejsapi=1&#038;autoplay=0&#038;cc_load_policy=0&#038;cc_lang_pref=&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;loop=0&#038;modestbranding=1&#038;rel=0&#038;fs=1&#038;playsinline=1&#038;autohide=1&#038;theme=light&#038;color=white&#038;controls=1&#038;" class="__youtube_prefs__  epyt-is-override  no-lazyload" title="YouTube player"  allow="fullscreen; accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen data-no-lazy="1" data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll=""></iframe></div><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282665 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193502-694x367.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="367" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193502-694x367.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193502.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282643 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0003-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0003-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0003.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282646 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0006-694x390.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="390" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0006-694x390.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0006.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><h2>90 年代的玩家日常：報攤上的《GAME WEEKLY》</h2><p>在 80、90 年代的香港，遊戲機盛行，但互聯網尚未普及。那時候，玩家要追蹤最新資訊和攻略，最簡單的方法就是購買遊戲雜誌。《GAME WEEKLY》成為報攤上最受歡迎的雜誌之一，定價僅十多港元，讓學生也負擔得起。無論是《Final Fantasy》的隱藏道具，還是《Street Fighter》的連招秘技，攻略內容為玩家提供了無數驚喜。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282647 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0015-694x385.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="385" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0015-694x385.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0015.jpg 1045w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p>電玩太郎分享：「早期的雜誌像份報紙，讀完後可以丟掉，但沒想到很多讀者會收藏，甚至從第一期到最後一期都保存下來。」這份情懷，讓不少人懷念起旺角和銅鑼灣街頭報攤前的排隊情景。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282645 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0002-2-618x580.jpg" alt="" width="618" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0002-2-618x580.jpg 618w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unwire0002-2.jpg 665w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 618px" /></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-medium wp-image-1282663 aligncenter" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193358-694x418.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="418" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193358-694x418.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/20241219193358.jpg 1280w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><br /><b>
]]>
            </description>
